      • RepeatingGroupAccessor

        @Deprecated
public RepeatingGroupAccessor(int parentNumInGroupTag,
                                          ITagValues parent,
                                          String msgType,
                                          String dictionaryName)
        Deprecated. 
        Constructor.
        Parameters:
        parentNumInGroupTag - The numInGroup tag number of parent. 35 if the parent is the message itself, or numInGroup tag of parent group in case of nested repeating groups.
        parent - The parent ITagValues. Can be the message itself, or a RepeatingGroupEntry in case of nested repeating groups
        msgType - FIX message type of message containing this group
        dictionaryName - FIX dictionary to look up the repeating group information

      • createRepeatingGroup

        public RepeatingGroup createRepeatingGroup(int tag)
                                    throws IllegalArgumentException,
                                           IllegalStateException
        Deprecated. 
        A new repeating group is created with the given numInGroup tag, added to the parent store, and returned.
        Specified by:
        createRepeatingGroup in interface IRepeatingGroupAccessor
        Parameters:
        tag - The tag identifying the repeating group according to the FIX spec (numInGroup tag)
        Returns:
        a repeating group with no entries (ie numInGroup tag = 0)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given tag is not valid for that particular message type according to the dictionary.
        IllegalStateException - If a group with the given tag already exists or if there's no message type or dictionary name specified.

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • setRepeatingGroup

        public void setRepeatingGroup(RepeatingGroup sourceGroup)
                       throws IllegalArgumentException
        Deprecated. 
        Adds a pre-existing repeating group to the parent store. If the group with the given tag does not yet exist in the store it is created, otherwise the existing group will be cleaned and its contents replaced with the new group's content. General validations against the dictionary are performed.
        Specified by:
        setRepeatingGroup in interface IRepeatingGroupAccessor
        Parameters:
        sourceGroup - Group to set
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the passed in repeating group is not valid for the parent store based on msg type and dictionary.
